Package: stannis
Type: Package
Title: Importance Sampling Type Correction of Markov Chain Monte Carlo with Stan
Version: 0.0.2
Date: 2017-06-13
Author: Jouni Helske
Maintainer: Jouni Helske <jouni.helske@iki.fi>
Description: The package provides an importance sampling type corrected Markov 
   chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) algorithm for structural Poisson time series, 
   where the MCMC is performed using Hamiltonian Monte Carlo provided by Stan, 
   and the correction is performed with particle filtering. The 
   package also contains a vignette providing a small simulation study which compares 
   variants of random-walk pseudo-marginal MCMC with HMC, and the IS-corrected versions of these.
License: GPL (>= 2)
Depends:
    R (>= 3.0.2),
    Rcpp (>= 0.12.9),
    methods,
Imports:
    bssm,
    coda,
    diagis,
    dplyr,
    rstan (>= 2.14.1)
LinkingTo: StanHeaders (>= 2.14.0.1), rstan (>= 2.14.1), BH (>= 1.62.0.1),
    RcppArmadillo, Rcpp (>= 0.12.9), RcppEigen (>= 0.3.2.9.0)
SystemRequirements: C++11
